race.comment: BUCK SHINES (7) turned in a plain effort last time when seventh at Ballarat over 450m behind Sunny Stride (26.21) in a Grade 5. Better than the latest effort and deserves another chance. SPICY SEDUCTION (2) copped a check in the run and finished a well held 12 lengths eighth (26.13) last time in a Grade 5 at this track over 450m. Better than last start and can bounce back. BARRY BALE (6) was prominent throughout when winning two back then got further back last time but came home hard into second and beaten 3.5 lengths at Ballarat (22.48). Form from his last run is proving to be solid. Expected to be in this for a long way. LITTLE MINNIE (1) can sneak into the finish with the right run.
